{% else -%}
[§ 20 Abs. 6 EStG](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/estg/__20.html) restricts loss-netting within capital income: **stock losses** may only offset **stock gains** (including across years via a loss carryforward), never other capital income. Other capital losses (funds, options, interest) net against each other. The BMF Abgeltungsteuer letter (margin numbers 120, 122, 228-230) governs the ordering.

This stage takes the stock gain from DE25-13, applies any 2024 stock-loss carryforward (capped by the current stock gain), and gathers the remaining positive capital income (funds after Teilfreistellung, options, interest, substitute payments) into the "non-stock" pool that the saver allowance at DE25-16 will reduce.

For 2025:

- Stock gain after applying carryforward ([§ 20 Abs. 6 EStG](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/estg/__20.html)): **{{ net.stock_gain_after_carryforward | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- Stock loss carryforward consumed from 2024: **{{ net.stock_loss_carryforward_used | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- Stock loss carryforward remaining for 2026: **{{ net.stock_loss_carryforward_remaining | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- Foreign tax per item (pooled by item ID for the DE25-18 per-item credit cap):
{% for item, value in net.foreign_tax_by_item.items() -%}
  - {{ item }}: **{{ value | money(currency="EUR") }}**
{% endfor -%}
- Foreign-tax refund entitlement per item:
{% for item, value in net.foreign_tax_refund_by_item.items() -%}
  - {{ item }}: **{{ value | money(currency="EUR") }}**
{% endfor -%}
- Taxable amount per item before the saver allowance (used to cap per-item credits):
{% for item, value in net.foreign_taxable_item_by_key_before_allowance.items() -%}
  - {{ item }}: **{{ value | money(currency="EUR") }}**
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

